Create IntelliJ Project
- Make sure it is Java version 11
- With a compatible spring version 2.4.9
- other than main dependencies spring-boot-starter-data-mongodb is needed

Create Collections in MongoDb
- Make sure to create cluster, database, collection in the Mongodb atlas cloud
- connect with credentials and the given uri from the atlas cloud and set it to the application.properties file
- Also make sure that the env variable is set to the running java version (11)

Create Application
- Use Rest Apis, Spring Data Jpa fro dev and postman for testing
- Rest apis for get list of,get one, create, update , delete todoos
- Validate necessaries. (Validate thorough : spring-started-validation, Mongo validation Config & Custom exception
- Do the necessities to all CRUD Operations
